WEBVTT

00:00.545 --> 00:03.718
‐(shrieking)
‐(woman screams)

00:03.751 --> 00:05.989
♪ ♪

00:12.101 --> 00:14.138
(birds chirping)

00:22.589 --> 00:24.593
(bird cawing)

00:28.433 --> 00:30.470
♪ ♪

00:42.461 --> 00:44.465
Are you sure
you two want to go in there?

00:44.499 --> 00:46.637
‐That place was built
above the devil's asshole.
‐That is why

00:46.670 --> 00:49.710
‐we are going in.
‐It's the most haunted house
in Los Angeles.

00:49.743 --> 00:51.614
Probably
the entire United States.

00:51.647 --> 00:54.686
Followed closely by the House
of Death in Greenwich Village,

00:54.720 --> 00:57.726
the Franklin Castle in Cleveland
and, of course...

00:57.759 --> 01:01.065
BOTH:
The LaLaurie Mansion
in New Orleans.

01:01.099 --> 01:03.403
Lies! Lies!

01:03.436 --> 01:05.073
(both laugh)

01:05.107 --> 01:08.146
We are, like,
huge American Horror Story fans.

01:08.179 --> 01:09.750
I hear bad stuff
about this house.

01:09.783 --> 01:11.520
How about I take you to a hotel?

01:11.553 --> 01:13.356
You mean like the Hotel Cortez?

01:13.390 --> 01:16.095
No, we're good. We rented
this place out for the night.

01:16.129 --> 01:18.400
‐It's an Airbnb now.
‐The owners offer

01:18.433 --> 01:21.105
this whole "Escape from
the Murder House Experience."

01:21.139 --> 01:22.542
It's supposed to be
super chilling.

01:22.575 --> 01:25.247
They promise
we will not sleep a wink.

01:25.280 --> 01:27.619
We're, like,
huge horror fans in general.

01:27.652 --> 01:29.155
We met a couple years back
at Comic‐Con.

01:29.188 --> 01:31.426
I was dressed
as Son of Bloody Face,

01:31.459 --> 01:33.631
and she was dressed
as Sister Jude.

01:34.666 --> 01:36.269
It was love at first sight.

01:36.302 --> 01:39.241
Whatever.
But don't say I didn't warn you.

01:49.195 --> 01:51.232
♪ ♪

02:05.828 --> 02:07.866
(Connie exhales)

02:08.834 --> 02:10.805
‐Wait.
‐What?

02:10.838 --> 02:13.209
‐You having second thoughts?
‐No.

02:13.243 --> 02:15.748
(chuckles):
No. I just want to feel it

02:15.782 --> 02:18.353
before all
the preplanned crazy starts.

02:18.386 --> 02:21.760
I just want to feel
the energy of the house.

02:22.729 --> 02:24.766
(exhales)

02:30.410 --> 02:33.450
‐(gasps)
‐What?

02:33.483 --> 02:35.655
(chuckles):
Nothing.

02:35.688 --> 02:37.291
Nothing.
I think I'm just so psyched,

02:37.324 --> 02:39.295
I'm getting
a bit ahead of myself.

02:39.328 --> 02:42.502
Come on. Let's go explore.

02:49.850 --> 02:52.388
"Welcome to Murder House.

02:52.421 --> 02:55.260
"If you're anything
like every other poor soul

02:55.293 --> 02:59.536
that entered these walls,
you may get stuck here forever."

02:59.569 --> 03:01.607
(Dylan chuckles)

03:01.640 --> 03:04.412
There's something
on the back of the note.

03:04.445 --> 03:06.215
"We hear you're 'Violataters.'

03:06.249 --> 03:08.286
"Your next adventure is to find

03:08.319 --> 03:10.792
"the room where Tate first
appeared to her and they later

03:10.825 --> 03:14.499
"consummated their forbidden
and fateful love.

03:14.533 --> 03:17.404
"Follow the black rose petals

03:17.438 --> 03:19.208
if you dare."

03:20.878 --> 03:22.849
Oh, my God. This is amazing.

03:22.882 --> 03:24.586
(chuckles softly):
Yeah.

03:26.590 --> 03:29.328
To the man
who makes my dreams come true,

03:29.361 --> 03:31.900
even if they're nightmares.

03:35.942 --> 03:37.344
DYLAN:
Oh.

03:37.377 --> 03:40.350
Tastes like... blood.

03:40.383 --> 03:41.653
Awesome.

03:45.628 --> 03:48.266
‐Let's play.
‐Yeah.

03:49.468 --> 03:50.671
(door creaks)

03:56.850 --> 03:58.888
♪ ♪

04:06.302 --> 04:09.275
(door creaks)

04:09.308 --> 04:10.711
This is so sick.

04:10.745 --> 04:13.751
Wait, who lit the candles?

04:13.784 --> 04:16.422
Do you think there's someone
in the house with us?

04:16.456 --> 04:18.828
There's got to be, right?
Like the haunted hayrides.

04:18.861 --> 04:20.898
I feel like
we should be prepared

04:20.932 --> 04:22.769
for a few jump scares.

04:22.802 --> 04:24.773
Wait, maybe they're
in the tunnels

04:24.806 --> 04:26.042
behind the walls.

04:26.075 --> 04:28.514
Uh, I think
that's just in the show.

04:28.547 --> 04:30.651
Don't think
that's actually in the house.

04:30.685 --> 04:32.454
Maybe it was Larry Harvey
and he used

04:32.488 --> 04:35.293
one of his smoldering children
to light them.

04:35.327 --> 04:37.364
Up for a little cosplay?

04:38.601 --> 04:39.870
Holy shit.

04:40.872 --> 04:41.907
(moans)

04:43.944 --> 04:45.581
(grunts)

04:45.615 --> 04:47.519
No, no, no, no. Leave it on.

04:47.552 --> 04:48.988
Kinky.

04:57.972 --> 05:00.010
(moaning)

05:06.022 --> 05:07.826
(grunts)

05:08.828 --> 05:10.865
Sorry.

05:14.840 --> 05:16.475
CONNIE:
Why do you think people like

05:16.510 --> 05:18.012
scary stories so much?

05:18.046 --> 05:21.352
Well, they always have.

05:21.385 --> 05:24.926
Pretend monsters let us forget
about the real ones.

05:24.960 --> 05:26.095
(shriek)

05:26.128 --> 05:27.699
ADDIE:
You're gonna die in here.

05:27.732 --> 05:30.505
(chuckles):
My gosh. There must be a speaker

05:30.538 --> 05:32.909
hidden somewhere in this room.
That is so cool.

05:38.787 --> 05:40.992
Do you think there's someone
in the house with us?

05:41.025 --> 05:43.396
‐Let's go see.
‐Okay.

05:48.172 --> 05:49.809
‐What's the matter?
‐I don't know.

05:49.843 --> 05:51.145
I can't seem to get up.

05:51.178 --> 05:52.849
What?

05:55.855 --> 05:57.792
‐(grunts)
‐(chuckles)

05:57.825 --> 05:59.796
‐(woman screams)
‐(chuckling)

05:59.829 --> 06:02.502
‐(Connie laughs)
‐Oh, my God.

06:02.535 --> 06:04.906
Come on, let's go check it out.

06:09.048 --> 06:10.551
Maybe I could find a ghost

06:10.585 --> 06:12.755
that'll last
more than two pumps.

06:16.597 --> 06:18.099
(mouths)

06:18.132 --> 06:19.468
‐(Connie exhales)
‐DYLAN: They based this episode

06:19.502 --> 06:20.805
‐on Richard Speck.
‐(screams)

06:20.838 --> 06:22.040
(Dylan chuckles softly)

06:22.074 --> 06:23.844
You know,

06:23.877 --> 06:25.982
he's the serial killer
that murdered all those nurses.

06:26.015 --> 06:27.552
Yeah. We met
at a horror convention.

06:27.585 --> 06:29.623
‐You think I don't know that?
‐Okay.

06:34.699 --> 06:35.935
‐Okay.
‐What?

06:35.968 --> 06:37.505
I'm guessing this is the part

06:37.538 --> 06:38.908
where we have to sign
all those waivers

06:38.941 --> 06:40.745
is gonna start.
"Warning. By signing this,

06:40.778 --> 06:42.582
"you accept
that you absolve all knowledge

06:42.615 --> 06:45.153
"of anything that can happen
to your mind, body or psyche

06:45.186 --> 06:47.157
"during your time
in the experience

06:47.190 --> 06:49.461
‐of the Escape from
the Murder House Experience."
‐I know.

06:49.496 --> 06:51.566
Just saying,
this is our last chance.

06:51.600 --> 06:53.704
You know, we could always go
to Norms, get some pancakes,

06:53.737 --> 06:55.775
go home, binge‐watch Roanoke.

06:55.808 --> 06:57.745
Why does Sarah Paulson
shit‐talk that season?

06:57.779 --> 06:59.148
It's so good.

06:59.181 --> 07:00.851
Do you really want
to go watch Roanoke?

07:00.885 --> 07:03.489
No. I want to shit myself
'cause I'm so scared.

07:03.524 --> 07:05.093
‐Me, too.
‐Come on.

07:05.126 --> 07:06.997
(stairs creaking)

07:09.903 --> 07:13.009
(screams, laughs)

07:26.035 --> 07:28.507
♪ ♪

07:32.548 --> 07:33.817
Come on.

07:35.253 --> 07:37.257
‐(grunts, chuckles)
‐(chuckles)

07:37.291 --> 07:38.894
‐(faint crying)
‐Shh.

07:38.927 --> 07:41.533
Do you hear that?

07:45.975 --> 07:47.979
‐Help us, please!
‐Please,

07:48.012 --> 07:49.783
‐help us!
‐Who the hell are they?

07:49.816 --> 07:51.018
Did we miss an episode?

07:51.052 --> 07:52.922
CONNIE:
I'm sorry, who are you?

07:52.955 --> 07:54.559
Yeah, sorry,
which episode are you guys from?

07:54.592 --> 07:55.928
What are you talking about?

07:55.961 --> 07:57.965
Ten years ago,
we went trick‐or‐treating.

07:59.602 --> 08:01.540
ALL:
Trick or treat.

08:01.573 --> 08:03.242
You girls don't want to be here.

08:03.276 --> 08:05.681
‐DILF alert.
‐(others giggle)

08:05.715 --> 08:07.150
MIKA:
You can give us some candy,

08:07.184 --> 08:10.156
but you can also
just invite us in for a treat.

08:10.190 --> 08:12.528
Leave now or else.

08:17.538 --> 08:21.012
Let's go inside and give him
a good Halloween scare.

08:22.682 --> 08:25.053
(door creaks)

08:27.892 --> 08:29.796
Where'd he go?

08:30.664 --> 08:32.034
(door closes)

08:34.271 --> 08:35.641
Did you see that?

08:35.674 --> 08:37.077
(women scream)

08:37.110 --> 08:38.312
RUBY:
Hi, ladies.

08:38.346 --> 08:41.252
Welcome to Murder House,

08:41.285 --> 08:43.690
where you can check in
anytime you like

08:43.724 --> 08:45.126
but you can never leave.

08:45.160 --> 08:47.598
(women screaming)

08:59.956 --> 09:01.993
You have to help us out of here.
Please.

09:02.027 --> 09:03.964
‐Please, help us.
‐They can't help us.

09:03.997 --> 09:05.601
No one can.

09:05.634 --> 09:07.304
We were killed here,
so we can never escape.

09:07.337 --> 09:09.041
Sorry, but she's right.

09:09.074 --> 09:11.580
If you die here,
you're trapped here forever.

09:11.613 --> 09:13.316
Maybe we're supposed to try
and help them, though.

09:13.349 --> 09:16.823
I mean, it is called the "Escape
from Murder House Experience."

09:16.857 --> 09:18.259
‐JANNA: Please.
‐KATE: Please, help us.

09:18.292 --> 09:20.698
It's the Infantata.

09:20.731 --> 09:22.635
(panting)

09:22.668 --> 09:24.706
‐(screeches)
‐(light buzzing)

09:24.739 --> 09:26.142
‐(Dylan grunts)
‐(women gasp)

09:26.175 --> 09:29.014
‐(panting)
‐Is that fake blood?

09:29.047 --> 09:32.354
‐It cut me.
It really fucking cut me.
‐This isn't right!

09:32.387 --> 09:35.160
‐Please, stop!
We don't like it! It's too much!
‐(Dylan grunts)

09:35.193 --> 09:37.364
And we want it to stop!
Please! Now!

09:37.397 --> 09:39.101
(screaming)

09:40.638 --> 09:43.944
Please, stop! We don't like it!
It's too real!

09:43.977 --> 09:45.714
You're not supposed to hurt us!

09:45.748 --> 09:47.752
It's not fake. It's real!

09:47.785 --> 09:49.354
‐Get out of here!
‐(shouts)

09:49.388 --> 09:51.058
Now!
(screams)

09:52.227 --> 09:53.831
(screams, grunts)

09:53.864 --> 09:56.001
(screaming)

09:59.976 --> 10:02.715
‐(gunshot)
‐No!

10:02.748 --> 10:04.719
No!

10:04.752 --> 10:07.190
I told you, dumb bitch.
You're gonna die in here.

10:07.224 --> 10:09.662
What are you doing here?
You died on the street!

10:09.696 --> 10:11.800
We've all come here
from all over.

10:11.833 --> 10:13.770
‐It's a special occasion.
‐What occasion?

10:13.804 --> 10:15.173
The day you die.

10:15.206 --> 10:17.110
(Addie chuckles)

10:18.279 --> 10:19.983
(screams)

10:20.016 --> 10:22.154
This isn't possible!

10:22.187 --> 10:23.690
None of you should be here!

10:23.724 --> 10:25.828
Please, make this stop!

10:25.861 --> 10:27.665
(screams)

10:28.432 --> 10:29.803
(whimpering)

10:36.448 --> 10:38.921
DEEP VOICE:
You were killed by Twisty.

10:38.954 --> 10:42.995
You are now trapped
in the Murder House forever.

10:43.029 --> 10:46.135
These controls suck.
It keeps glitching.

10:46.168 --> 10:48.105
I could have escaped,
but it froze up again right when

10:48.139 --> 10:50.043
‐I tried to run.
‐Okay. I mean, look,
that's an easy fix.

10:50.076 --> 10:51.847
But what do you think
in general?

10:51.880 --> 10:53.984
Come on, the graphics
are amazing, aren't they?

10:54.017 --> 10:55.788
(sighs)
Yeah.

10:55.821 --> 10:56.957
But?

10:56.990 --> 10:58.760
Don't take this the wrong way,

10:58.794 --> 11:01.666
but, like, have you even
ever actually watched the show?

11:01.700 --> 11:03.737
Yes, I've watched the show.
I'm not an obsessive fan

11:03.770 --> 11:05.875
like you, but...
I've watched the show.

11:05.908 --> 11:08.045
Even casual fans of the show
are gonna be pissed

11:08.079 --> 11:09.749
because Addie is a ghost there

11:09.782 --> 11:11.318
and there are other characters
from other seasons

11:11.352 --> 11:13.022
who have no business
being there.

11:13.055 --> 11:14.993
Second, I think
you're missing the reason

11:15.026 --> 11:17.464
why fans keep wanting
to go back to Murder House.

11:17.498 --> 11:19.301
It's not that they want
to trap more people there.

11:19.334 --> 11:21.907
They want to feel the tension
of whether or not

11:21.940 --> 11:23.944
the new people are gonna be able
to escape or not.

11:23.977 --> 11:25.881
The thing that always
trips people up in the house

11:25.915 --> 11:28.352
and leads them down that path
to getting stuck there

11:28.386 --> 11:30.123
is that they don't deal
with their human shit.

11:30.156 --> 11:32.695
They're too selfish or greedy

11:32.728 --> 11:34.966
or mean or possessive
or depressed,

11:34.999 --> 11:36.202
so they're forced
to stay like that,

11:36.235 --> 11:37.772
frozen in the house forever.

11:37.805 --> 11:39.208
Okay, I hear you.

11:39.241 --> 11:40.778
But it's scary.

11:40.811 --> 11:42.347
‐(sighs)
‐Right? Isn't it enough

11:42.380 --> 11:45.220
if‐if it's in the same
basic setting but it's scary?

11:45.253 --> 11:47.123
(sighs)
I don't know.

11:47.157 --> 11:50.798
That's exactly what the people
who made Jaws 2 thought.

11:50.831 --> 11:53.336
‐(sighs)
‐Okay. Um...

11:55.173 --> 11:57.143
I put everything into this.

11:57.177 --> 12:00.350
I quit my job to develop it.
I mortgaged the house

12:00.383 --> 12:02.087
so that I could hire
the programmers

12:02.120 --> 12:03.790
who have been working
in our garage day and night.

12:03.824 --> 12:07.030
I need this to work out for us.
For our family.

12:07.063 --> 12:11.138
‐I didn't ask you
to do any of this.
‐I did this

12:11.171 --> 12:12.808
for you because I thought...

12:12.842 --> 12:15.781
I thought we could bond
over your favorite show.

12:15.814 --> 12:17.852
You could've just watched it
with me.

12:17.885 --> 12:21.025
I love you, Mom, but you don't
really get the vibe of the show.

12:21.058 --> 12:23.964
Like... at all.

12:25.433 --> 12:28.507
You're saying
I don't get you at all.

12:28.540 --> 12:30.343
(scoffs)

12:30.376 --> 12:32.213
I'm trying.

12:33.182 --> 12:34.418
Wait, honey.
Where are you going?

12:34.451 --> 12:37.223
I got HiHo burgers
from Postmates.

12:37.257 --> 12:39.227
Where you going?

12:39.261 --> 12:41.131
I'm gonna stay at Dad's tonight.

12:41.165 --> 12:44.304
Actually, I think I'm gonna stay
there for a couple of weeks.

12:44.338 --> 12:46.041
Things have gotten

12:46.075 --> 12:48.847
so weird around here lately.

12:49.816 --> 12:52.855
‐Rory.
‐(sighs)

12:56.896 --> 12:58.332
(sighs)

13:05.046 --> 13:06.448
♪ ♪

13:16.335 --> 13:17.404
DEEP VOICE:
Garden shears.

13:37.077 --> 13:38.379
♪ ♪

13:48.132 --> 13:50.269
(panting)

14:09.976 --> 14:12.180
DEEP VOICE:
There's no escape.

14:24.539 --> 14:26.576
(squealing)

14:44.311 --> 14:46.315
♪ ♪

14:55.299 --> 14:58.105
♪ ♪

15:07.056 --> 15:08.527
(door creaks)

15:11.331 --> 15:12.333
‐(thud on TV)
‐(screams)

15:18.479 --> 15:21.218
♪ ♪

15:26.128 --> 15:28.365
TIM:
Usually I wait
until the end of the tour

15:28.399 --> 15:30.436
to give the bad news, but...

15:30.470 --> 15:33.610
why bother delaying
the inevitable? (clears throat)

15:33.643 --> 15:36.516
They found nine bodies
in the house a year or so ago.

15:36.549 --> 15:38.520
MICHELLE:
I know.

15:38.553 --> 15:41.593
And I know about the body
of that girl Ruby McDaniel

15:41.626 --> 15:43.362
they found in the backyard
a month later.

15:43.395 --> 15:46.468
(sighs)
Oh, God.

15:46.503 --> 15:48.139
You're not
one of those murder nerds

15:48.172 --> 15:50.276
who's just here
to take Instagram selfies

15:50.309 --> 15:52.147
inside the house?
Because I know.

15:52.180 --> 15:54.685
I know this is the shittiest
listing in America, and I know

15:54.719 --> 15:57.223
that it says a lot about what
the other agents at my office

15:57.257 --> 15:58.994
think about me that I'm the one
who's stuck with it,

15:59.027 --> 16:01.533
but I'm sorry.
I take my job seriously.

16:01.566 --> 16:03.402
To me, every listing

16:03.435 --> 16:06.375
is‐is a little orphan child
looking for a new family

16:06.408 --> 16:08.613
to adopt it. And, yes,
this one has some baggage

16:08.647 --> 16:10.116
and some real issues,

16:10.149 --> 16:12.220
but it is no less deserving
of love.

16:12.253 --> 16:14.124
‐How much?
‐Seriously?

16:14.157 --> 16:15.359
It's an investment.

16:15.393 --> 16:18.299
Okay. Uh, well, you're in luck.

16:18.332 --> 16:21.305
The bank is basically willing
to sell it for land value.

16:21.338 --> 16:22.575
How much is that?

16:22.608 --> 16:24.277
$600,000.

16:24.311 --> 16:26.716
But, unfortunately for them,

16:26.749 --> 16:28.319
no one's been willing
to pay that,

16:28.352 --> 16:31.993
‐so they are open to any offers.
‐$100,000.

16:36.034 --> 16:37.437
I need to make a call,

16:37.470 --> 16:38.673
but I think you
just bought yourself a house.

16:38.707 --> 16:41.278
As is, of course.

16:41.311 --> 16:42.648
This thing is harder to move

16:42.681 --> 16:45.319
‐than a toxic waste dump.
‐(phone clicks, beeps)

16:45.353 --> 16:48.593
Jenny? Hi. Hi.
Yeah, I think I found someone

16:48.627 --> 16:51.164
to adopt
our little devil baby house.

16:51.198 --> 16:53.202
No contingencies.

16:53.235 --> 16:56.008
♪ ♪

17:00.116 --> 17:02.621
You're mine.

17:02.655 --> 17:06.696
I am going to make you reveal
all your secrets to me.

17:19.789 --> 17:22.360
(chuckles):
Rory. Honey, you look so cute.

17:22.393 --> 17:24.632
‐Look at you.
‐RORY: Mom.

17:24.665 --> 17:27.370
‐What are you doing here?
‐Oh, um, I just brought you
some extra clothes.

17:27.403 --> 17:29.241
I am gonna be going away
for about a week or so.

17:29.274 --> 17:30.644
Where?

17:30.677 --> 17:32.648
I'm going to
a Halloween horror convention.

17:32.681 --> 17:35.386
The writers of American
Horror Story are doing a talk.

17:35.419 --> 17:37.190
I'm gonna ask them to tell me
all about Murder House.

17:37.223 --> 17:39.461
What it means, what
the most important aspects are.

17:39.495 --> 17:40.764
Hey, I'm taking your advice.

17:40.797 --> 17:42.433
I'm trying to figure out
the vibe.

17:42.467 --> 17:44.037
Right from the horse's mouth.

17:45.273 --> 17:47.310
‐Steven.
‐Michelle.

17:48.613 --> 17:50.383
I'm sorry, I just overheard

17:50.416 --> 17:51.653
‐what you were telling Rory.
‐Yeah, I'm sorry, too,

17:51.686 --> 17:52.721
'cause it's none
