‐Hey. Hey.
‐What?

32:02.520 --> 32:04.991
Why aren't you dressed up?
(chuckles)

32:05.025 --> 32:06.662
I don't like Halloween anymore.

32:15.345 --> 32:17.349
♪ ♪

32:40.028 --> 32:42.099
♪ ♪

33:02.406 --> 33:04.143
You guys coming inside?

33:04.176 --> 33:06.715
‐We like to do it our own way.
‐Hey.

33:06.748 --> 33:08.284
Sorry about trapping you
in there.

33:09.286 --> 33:12.292
You held the knife,
but I did it to myself, really.

33:16.300 --> 33:18.271
Ten seconds to sunrise.

33:18.304 --> 33:20.342
♪ ♪

33:50.202 --> 33:52.172
♪ ♪

34:20.630 --> 34:22.065
(dog barking in distance)

34:22.099 --> 34:25.205
(liquid sloshing)

34:28.512 --> 34:31.317
‐The fuck is this?
‐Oh, no.

34:31.350 --> 34:33.856
‐RUBY: You know him?
‐MICHELLE: He's my son.

34:33.889 --> 34:35.392
He's trying
to burn the house down.

34:35.425 --> 34:37.597
Thinks it's gonna free
all the spirits.

34:37.630 --> 34:38.666
Will it?

34:38.699 --> 34:40.536
God, I hope so.

34:40.569 --> 34:42.372
Well, what about those of us
who don't want to be free?

34:43.441 --> 34:45.245
I do not need this shit today.

34:47.850 --> 34:50.690
MICHELLE:
Rory.

34:50.723 --> 34:52.827
I think you and your son
should really consider

34:52.860 --> 34:54.731
some family therapy. Now,
I know that you've already met

34:54.764 --> 34:56.635
with Ben Harmon,
but I can assure you

34:56.668 --> 34:58.271
‐you'll see much better
results with me.
‐Move.

34:58.304 --> 34:59.541
Quite frankly,
he's just not that good.

34:59.574 --> 35:00.876
(chuckles)

35:00.910 --> 35:02.880
I'm available anytime.

35:02.914 --> 35:05.118
♪ ♪

35:07.724 --> 35:09.561
RUBY:
I'm gonna gut him but make sure
he bleeds out slowly enough

35:09.594 --> 35:11.832
to throw him off the property.
The last thing we need is

35:11.865 --> 35:14.136
another troublemaker in here.
‐GLADYS: No!

35:14.169 --> 35:16.541
(Gladys grunts)

35:19.179 --> 35:20.583
Sorry, Ruby.

35:20.616 --> 35:23.187
What you and Scarlett had
was so lovely,

35:23.221 --> 35:24.924
but it's time for us to go now.

35:24.958 --> 35:26.460
(grunting)

35:29.701 --> 35:31.672
We can't take it anymore.

35:31.705 --> 35:34.276
‐I just need it to be over.
‐RUBY: You stupid bitches.

35:34.310 --> 35:35.913
Don't you understand
what that means?

35:35.946 --> 35:37.850
It means we become nothing!

35:37.884 --> 35:40.723
Nothing is better than this
for all eternity.

35:40.756 --> 35:42.292
(Ruby grunts)

35:44.698 --> 35:45.833
Attaboy.

35:45.866 --> 35:48.304
Burn, baby, burn.

35:48.338 --> 35:50.810
‐MAYA: Dr. Harmon.
‐(Ruby gasping)

35:54.884 --> 35:57.757
And the record kept skipping

35:57.790 --> 36:00.830
over and over...

36:02.299 --> 36:04.370
...and over.

36:06.374 --> 36:08.177
(coughing)

36:08.211 --> 36:09.681
Sorry. Not sorry.

36:12.653 --> 36:15.191
(lighter flicks)

36:15.225 --> 36:18.331
(Ruby gasping, coughing)

36:25.913 --> 36:28.852
Yeah, can I get a breakfast
burrito, a fresh orange juice,

36:28.886 --> 36:31.591
‐oh, and an apple pie?
‐(phone chimes)

36:35.666 --> 36:36.868
(tires screech)

36:38.906 --> 36:40.810
(tires squealing)

36:41.778 --> 36:44.383
Are you sure
this is what you want?

36:44.416 --> 36:45.485
Yes.

36:47.623 --> 36:50.629
Guess you figured out a way
to end the video game.

36:50.663 --> 36:52.633
It'll be a best seller.

36:52.667 --> 36:53.902
I'm sure of it.

36:55.906 --> 36:57.944
(Rory sighs)

36:57.977 --> 36:59.647
Goodbye, Mom.

37:00.716 --> 37:02.520
(crying):
Bye, my sweet boy.

37:02.553 --> 37:04.256
‐(screams)
‐Mom!

37:04.289 --> 37:05.960
MICHELLE:
No! Do it! Light it up!

37:05.993 --> 37:08.532
Do it, baby, do it!

37:08.565 --> 37:10.770
‐(grunts)
‐(Michelle screams)

37:20.589 --> 37:22.693
(Ruby grunts)

37:22.727 --> 37:25.398
No! No! No!

37:26.467 --> 37:27.970
‐No!
‐No!

37:28.004 --> 37:29.874
(panting)
Please.

37:30.943 --> 37:32.647
‐(crying): No!
‐(whispers): Do it.

37:33.582 --> 37:35.820
Do it!

37:41.698 --> 37:43.434
(grunting)

37:47.309 --> 37:49.848
♪ ♪

37:49.881 --> 37:51.417
Ruby!

37:53.488 --> 37:54.958
RUBY (crying):
Scarlett.

37:57.763 --> 37:59.466
Die with me!

37:59.501 --> 38:01.872
(crying)

38:01.905 --> 38:03.942
♪ ♪

38:20.910 --> 38:23.682
(mouths)

38:46.060 --> 38:48.632
MAN: Well, the ghosts
weren't the problem.

38:48.665 --> 38:50.569
It was the damn TV show fans

38:50.603 --> 38:52.907
that kept coming here
at all hours to take selfies.

38:52.940 --> 38:54.511
Hey, assholes,

38:54.544 --> 38:55.746
it's just a house.

38:55.779 --> 38:57.482
NEWSWOMAN:
The fire is out

38:57.517 --> 38:58.919
except for
some smoldering remnants.

38:58.952 --> 39:00.656
And just like that,

39:00.689 --> 39:03.896
one of the most notorious houses
in all of Los Angeles‐‐

39:03.929 --> 39:07.102
maybe the world‐‐
is finally gone for good.

39:16.186 --> 39:18.391
♪ ♪

39:35.559 --> 39:37.663
(buttons beeping)

39:37.697 --> 39:39.534
(lock buzzes)

39:44.076 --> 39:46.948
‐You must be Scarlett.
‐Yes. Hi.

39:46.982 --> 39:49.419
Let me show you the unit.

39:50.956 --> 39:52.927
As you can see, the developers

39:52.960 --> 39:54.831
spared no expense.

39:54.864 --> 39:57.703
Everything in this unit
is state‐of‐the‐art,

39:57.737 --> 40:00.408
and these are divine.

40:00.441 --> 40:02.412
‐The architect went...
‐Tim.

40:02.445 --> 40:04.817
Can we have
an honest relationship?

40:04.851 --> 40:06.788
(chuckles):
Yeah, okay.

40:06.821 --> 40:08.090
Do you tell people

40:08.124 --> 40:10.863
who are looking
at these new condo units

40:10.896 --> 40:12.833
that these grounds are hallowed?

40:12.867 --> 40:14.537
Hallowed?

40:14.570 --> 40:16.473
Well,
dozens of people died here.

40:16.508 --> 40:18.210
People who mattered.

40:18.244 --> 40:19.681
Until the fire.

40:19.714 --> 40:21.483
Do you tell potential buyers

40:21.518 --> 40:24.724
that this building
of condominiums

40:24.757 --> 40:26.828
used to be the Murder House?

40:26.861 --> 40:28.832
(chuckles softly)

40:28.865 --> 40:31.203
Actually, no.

40:31.236 --> 40:32.607
No, I don't.

40:32.640 --> 40:34.844
‐Why not?
‐Well, to be honest‐‐

40:34.877 --> 40:37.148
since that's
what we're aiming for‐‐

40:37.182 --> 40:38.619
at first,

40:38.652 --> 40:40.088
I was torn.

40:40.121 --> 40:41.992
I sold the first five units,
and I said nothing

40:42.025 --> 40:44.964
about that place
that used to be here.

40:44.998 --> 40:48.605
But people have been living
in this new building now

40:48.639 --> 40:51.611
for over six months,
and I check in on my customers.

40:51.645 --> 40:53.047
No one has been harmed.

40:53.080 --> 40:55.753
There have been
no apparition sightings.

40:57.757 --> 40:59.494
I believe

40:59.527 --> 41:02.967
that the fire purified
whatever occult forces

41:03.000 --> 41:05.639
were contained
within those walls.

41:05.673 --> 41:08.144
And I also believe
that those spirits

41:08.177 --> 41:10.649
or whatever
you want to call them

41:10.683 --> 41:12.085
are finally free.

41:16.961 --> 41:20.168
And this is the last unit,
correct?

41:20.201 --> 41:21.270
Yeah.

41:21.303 --> 41:23.007
I'll take it.

41:23.040 --> 41:25.178
All cash.

41:25.211 --> 41:26.881
You'll pay $1 million

41:26.915 --> 41:28.685
all cash?

41:28.719 --> 41:30.288
A young woman your age?

41:30.321 --> 41:33.862
I'm sorry, may I ask
how you got that kind of money?

41:33.895 --> 41:36.801
I utilized
my greatest life skill

41:36.835 --> 41:38.805
and became a hired assassin.

41:38.839 --> 41:40.676
I'm semiretired now.

41:40.709 --> 41:42.880
Maybe I'll go back to it
one day. Who knows?

41:42.913 --> 41:44.951
But it was lucrative

41:44.984 --> 41:48.190
and fun killing bad people.

41:48.224 --> 41:50.662
(chuckles nervously)

41:50.696 --> 41:52.232
Don't look so shocked, Tim.
I told you

41:52.265 --> 41:55.739
‐I wanted
an honest relationship.
‐(chuckles)

41:58.244 --> 41:59.981
Okay, Scarlett.

42:00.014 --> 42:03.655
I'll draw up the papers.
This unit is officially yours.

42:10.134 --> 42:13.809
("Ghost" by Noah Cyrus playing)

42:14.877 --> 42:18.117
♪ Why don't we take a walk? ♪

42:18.150 --> 42:22.693
♪ Everybody knows
a hand to hold is all we need ♪

42:24.096 --> 42:26.968
♪ Quiet, let's not even talk ♪

42:27.001 --> 42:29.139
♪ Every word I say to you ♪

42:29.172 --> 42:32.580
♪ You only just repeat ♪

42:32.613 --> 42:35.753
♪ And when you're looking
in the mirror ♪

42:35.786 --> 42:41.096
♪ Demons may be closer
than they may appear ♪

42:41.130 --> 42:45.271
♪ You can either cry
and sit and stare ♪

42:45.304 --> 42:47.877
♪ Or try to run away ♪

42:47.910 --> 42:49.981
♪ I'm trying to run away ♪

42:50.014 --> 42:54.924
♪ I'm staring at a ghost ♪

42:59.199 --> 43:04.142
♪ I'm staring at a ghost ♪

43:14.296 --> 43:17.603
♪ And when you're looking
in the mirror ♪

43:17.636 --> 43:22.646
♪ Demons may be closer
than they may appear ♪

43:22.680 --> 43:26.921
♪ You can either cry
and sit and stare ♪

43:26.955 --> 43:29.192
♪ Or try to run away ♪

43:29.226 --> 43:31.063
♪ I'm trying to run away ♪

43:31.096 --> 43:33.267
♪ I'm staring at a ghost. ♪

43:33.300 --> 43:35.004
Ruby?

43:36.841 --> 43:38.879
I'm here.

43:39.981 --> 43:43.287
I'm finally ready
to be with you.

43:43.320 --> 43:45.324
Forever.

43:49.299 --> 43:51.838
(crying):
But I'm too late.

43:52.973 --> 43:56.013
(sniffles)
You're gone forever.

44:17.288 --> 44:18.324
(gasps)

44:18.357 --> 44:20.996
(panting)

44:26.006 --> 44:27.308
Where are the others?

44:27.342 --> 44:28.812
My dads?

44:29.847 --> 44:30.983
They're gone.

44:31.016 --> 44:33.120
They chose to move on.

44:33.153 --> 44:35.859
I saw them go.

44:35.893 --> 44:40.001
They seemed happy.
Most of them did, at least.

44:40.034 --> 44:41.804
Why are you still here?

44:41.838 --> 44:45.478
I was the only one
who wanted to stay.

44:45.512 --> 44:48.017
For you, Scarlett.

44:48.050 --> 44:51.189
I knew you'd come back to me.

44:52.526 --> 44:54.329
True love never dies.

44:57.302 --> 45:00.208
♪ ♪

45:03.180 --> 45:05.953
(fireworks popping)

45:09.292 --> 45:12.232
DEEP VOICE: Success.
You escaped Murder House.

45:12.265 --> 45:13.434
Oh!

45:13.467 --> 45:15.171
MICHELLE:
So? What do you think?

45:15.204 --> 45:17.776
Version 2.0.
I mean, does it get the vibe?

45:17.810 --> 45:20.916
Totally. It's so much better.

45:20.949 --> 45:23.287
‐(chuckles)
‐But I think
you need to have a level

45:23.320 --> 45:25.324
where the kid gets, like,
a magic potion

45:25.358 --> 45:26.895
from the Supremes

45:26.928 --> 45:29.165
to help burn the house down
or‐or something.

45:29.199 --> 45:31.504
I'd like to see that. I think
it'd make the game harder.

45:31.537 --> 45:33.307
I mean,
I‐I couldn't afford it, so...

45:33.340 --> 45:35.512
If we sell it, though,
we can maybe do it as an update

45:35.545 --> 45:38.752
‐or something.
‐Well, at least you fixed
the glitches in the controls.

45:38.785 --> 45:40.454
‐Oh, did I?
Did I fix the glitches?
‐(laughs)

45:40.488 --> 45:41.925
Yes, I insisted on it.

45:41.958 --> 45:43.427
You really like it?

45:43.460 --> 45:45.799
‐It's super cool.
‐(chuckles)

45:45.832 --> 45:47.201
And I'm really proud of you.

45:47.235 --> 45:49.472
Thank you, baby.

45:49.507 --> 45:52.045
‐Want to play again?
‐No.

45:52.078 --> 45:54.817
‐I think I've spent enough time
in the Murder House.
‐(chuckles)

45:54.850 --> 45:56.821
Do you want to go
get something to eat?

45:56.854 --> 45:58.490
‐Yeah, I'm starving.
‐Let's go.

45:58.525 --> 46:01.330
But where do you think

46:01.363 --> 46:02.800
all of the spirits
who got trapped

46:02.833 --> 46:04.069
in the Murder House went?

46:04.102 --> 46:05.338
The ones
who wanted to stay stayed,

46:05.371 --> 46:07.475
and the ones
who wanted to move on,

46:07.509 --> 46:10.014
they maybe went to heaven
or hell.

46:10.047 --> 46:12.418
Well, do you think any of them
escaped into the world?

46:12.452 --> 46:14.757
‐Hope not.
‐Hmm.

46:19.500 --> 46:21.537
♪ ♪

